verses.text_plain: Now concerning the collection for the saints, as I have given order to the churches of Galatia, even so do ye.
verses.verse_html: 1Now concerning the collection for the saints, as I have given order to the churches of Galatia, even so do ye.

verses.text_plain: Upon the first day of the week let every one of you lay by him in store, as God hath prospered him, that there be no gatherings when I come.
verses.verse_html: 2Upon the first day of the week let every one of you lay by him in store, as God hath prospered him, that there be no gatherings when I come.

verses.text_plain: And when I come, whomsoever ye shall approve by your letters, them will I send to bring your liberality unto Jerusalem.
verses.verse_html: 3And when I come, whomsoever ye shall approve by your letters, them will I send to bring your liberality unto Jerusalem.

verses.text_plain: And if it be meet that I go also, they shall go with me.
verses.verse_html: 4And if it be meet that I go also, they shall go with me.

verses.text_plain: Now I will come unto you, when I shall pass through Macedonia: for I do pass through Macedonia.
verses.verse_html: 5Now I will come unto you, when I shall pass through Macedonia: for I do pass through Macedonia.

verses.text_plain: And it may be that I will abide, yea, and winter with you, that ye may bring me on my journey whithersoever I go.
verses.verse_html: 6And it may be that I will abide, yea, and winter with you, that ye may bring me on my journey whithersoever I go.

verses.text_plain: For I will not see you now by the way; but I trust to tarry a while with you, if the Lord permit.
verses.verse_html: 7For I will not see you now by the way; but I trust to tarry a while with you, if the Lord permit.

verses.text_plain: But I will tarry at Ephesus until Pentecost.
verses.verse_html: 8But I will tarry at Ephesus until Pentecost.

verses.text_plain: For a great door and effectual is opened unto me, and there are many adversaries.
verses.verse_html: 9For a great door and effectual is opened unto me, and there are many adversaries.

verses.text_plain: Now if Timotheus come, see that he may be with you without fear: for he worketh the work of the Lord, as I also do.
verses.verse_html: 10Now if Timotheus come, see that he may be with you without fear: for he worketh the work of the Lord, as I also do.

verses.text_plain: Let no man therefore despise him: but conduct him forth in peace, that he may come unto me: for I look for him with the brethren.
verses.verse_html: 11Let no man therefore despise him: but conduct him forth in peace, that he may come unto me: for I look for him with the brethren.

verses.text_plain: As touching our brother Apollos, I greatly desired him to come unto you with the brethren: but his will was not at all to come at this time; but he will come when he shall have convenient time.
verses.verse_html: 12As touching our brother Apollos, I greatly desired him to come unto you with the brethren: but his will was not at all to come at this time; but he will come when he shall have convenient time.

verses.text_plain: Watch ye, stand fast in the faith, quit you like men, be strong.
verses.verse_html: 13Watch ye, stand fast in the faith, quit you like men, be strong.

verses.text_plain: Let all your things be done with charity.
verses.verse_html: 14Let all your things be done with charity.

verses.text_plain: I beseech you, brethren, (ye know the house of Stephanas, that it is the firstfruits of Achaia, and that they have addicted themselves to the ministry of the saints,)
verses.verse_html: 15I beseech you, brethren, (ye know the house of Stephanas, that it is the firstfruits of Achaia, and that they have addicted themselves to the ministry of the saints,)

verses.text_plain: That ye submit yourselves unto such, and to every one that helpeth with us, and laboureth.
verses.verse_html: 16That ye submit yourselves unto such, and to every one that helpeth with us, and laboureth.

verses.text_plain: I am glad of the coming of Stephanas and Fortunatus and Achaicus: for that which was lacking on your part they have supplied.
verses.verse_html: 17I am glad of the coming of Stephanas and Fortunatus and Achaicus: for that which was lacking on your part they have supplied.

verses.text_plain: For they have refreshed my spirit and yours: therefore acknowledge ye them that are such.
verses.verse_html: 18For they have refreshed my spirit and yours: therefore acknowledge ye them that are such.

verses.text_plain: The churches of Asia salute you. Aquila and Priscilla salute you much in the Lord, with the church that is in their house.
verses.verse_html: 19The churches of Asia salute you. Aquila and Priscilla salute you much in the Lord, with the church that is in their house.

verses.text_plain: All the brethren greet you. Greet ye one another with an holy kiss.
verses.verse_html: 20All the brethren greet you. Greet ye one another with an holy kiss.

verses.text_plain: The salutation of me Paul with mine own hand.
verses.verse_html: 21The salutation of me Paul with mine own hand.

verses.text_plain: If any man love not the Lord Jesus Christ, let him be Anathema Maran-atha.
verses.verse_html: 22If any man love not the Lord Jesus Christ, let him be Anathema Maran-atha.

verses.text_plain: The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.
verses.verse_html: 23The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.

verses.text_plain: My love be with you all in Christ Jesus. Amen. The first epistle to the Corinthians was written from Philippi by Stephanas, and Fortunatus, and Achaicus, and Timotheus.
verses.verse_html: 24My love be with you all in Christ Jesus. Amen. The first epistle to the Corinthians was written from Philippi by Stephanas, and Fortunatus, and Achaicus, and Timotheus.
